searchInboxes.name: The Shalizi Group
searchInboxes.description:
The Shalizi Group has quickly become one of the top entertainment and management companies in the industry. We live to break boundaries which has allowed us to manage some of the top multi-genre recording artists, DJ/Producers, and songwriters which includes household names such as Marshmello, Alesso, Afrojack, Jauz, Southside, Svdden Death and more. We support our growing roster through specialized in-house teams dedicated to talent management, digital marketing, merchandising, design, label services and brand development.  TSG has partnerships with leaders in gaming, television, technology, consumer goods, fashion, and digital marketing, creating an ever-evolving platform for the success of our clients.

In essence: Think. Strategize. Go.

Our inbox is open to receive Demo submissions from potential management artists or for release on one of our in-house dance labels

searchInboxes.name: NEED
searchInboxes.description:
NEED is an independent record label based in Amsterdam. Established in 2020, its founders set out to create a platform that would represent the full spectrum of house music beyond the boundaries of its subgenres. They saw this as a need for the industry, which would become the inspiration for the imprint’s name. 

Much like its native city, NEED has a dancefloor focus and welcomes different cultural influences to showcase their styles and sounds. The label is dedicated to supporting both local and international talent, from new to established names. 
NEED understands the importance of a progressive approach that covers digital and physical releases, streaming, vinyl, showcases and hostings to make sure great music makes an even greater impact.

searchInboxes.name: DJ 7OLF
searchInboxes.description:
DJ 7OLF discovered his passion for music from a young age, dedicating himself to studying various musical instruments. Fascinated by the world of mixing, he began by creating playlists for friends’ parties. At just fourteen, he embarked on a formative collaboration with his mentor, DJ Delta, an internationally renowned artist who taught him the basics of mixing and scratching.

His sound evolved under the influence of the overseas music scene, which he embraced and shared with the public. In the following years, DJ 7OLF began performing publicly, gracing the stages of festivals like Alcart and Numen Fest, and actively participating in the local music scene across Trapani, Palermo, and Catania. This journey led him to become a cornerstone of the Sicilian music scene.

In 2019, he founded NoEtiquette alongside other DJs and friends, aiming to revive the electronic music scene in West Sicily. The initiative received a strong response and significant interest from the public, further solidifying his position in the local music landscape.

With a decade of experience behind him, since 2018 he has been living and continuing his career in Milan. Here, he collaborated with ID Italy from Vice during the 2020 Fashion Week and internationally with the collective Esco UK. He continues his work as a DJ, performing in discos, clubs, and private parties, with DJ sets always full of energy. His fresh and innovative style engages and surprises audiences at every performance.

Parallel to his DJ career, DJ 7OLF dedicates himself to producing original tracks, with three releases to his name. This commitment to music production expands his contribution to contemporary electronic music, allowing him to fully express his creativity and artistic vision.

searchInboxes.name: SIDEY
searchInboxes.description: One of the rising stars in Melbourne's world renowned minimal scene, SIDEY toured the country and played abroad under his birthname, Eric Sidey. With passions shifting he felt it was time to make a shift of his own, dropping the 'Eric' and maximizing the caps to represent this new sound. SIDEY is an opportunity for this young producer to bring a maximalist sound and energy to clubs, festivals and car stereos.
